reviews.review_text: Joani Walker + Charlie Miller = WOW I can't recommend this recording enough.  As a former SBD-snob, I was skeptical that any audience recording could sway me away from my SBD ways... This set of recordings made by Walker-Scotton (processed by Charlie) are unbelievable.  Just take a listen.  The sound is full and deep, not thin and raspy.  The bass is rich, the highs are crisp.  The show is fantastic too, but the sound blows me away.
I Concur Thanks Charlie!  This is a definite upgrade over the previous AUD.

Drums/Space/chasnting >The Other One Well, this show, the Drums > Space just rules - anybody catch the small Cumberland Blues tease at the beginning of space? We got this tape 8 months before they broke out Cumby in Long Beach the following Summer & heard the tease before that - odd coincidence if coincidence it was.

The Wheel before drums is so sweet going into D/S & The Other One after the killer Drums/Space/chanting is odd in that Phil BLASTS the band into a third instrumental after verse two that tears the roof off the joint.

Totally forgotten show for these days, but GREAT
Big Brent in Big River Killer Brent solo in the middle of Big River....

wow, what a show and pristine aud recording this show gets five stars just for the incendiary other one out of a very cool space. kudos to joani walker and charlie miller for this wonderfully articulate and mixed recording.

Another Great Show From Late 1980 I still remember my friends reporting back from this gig - just how amazing the entire show was, not to mention Airto and Flora during drums.  And who can argue with a 12-song first set!  :)

Aaaaaaaaaaaand we're off!  Seldom does a show start with such a bang.  Absolute detonation into Bertha and it just goes.  They stride the musical landscape as colossal beasts.  Don't listen to this while driving - you could die...........

1980- -the beginning of my grad school concert slowdown After leaving college in Atlanta, I headed to Lincoln, NE for law school at U of N.   Thus began what I call the lean years....  Caught the May shows at Nassau Coliseum while home to Jersey for the summer.   And caught one of the Radio City Shows.   Other than that, my only shows until I returned to the east coast after graduating in May of 1983 were Des Moines on 12/7/81 and Iowa City on 8/10/82.  Listening to this one reminds me why I wanted to take a year off between college and law school!!!  Crackling with energy through and through.  And, as usual, Charlie and Joni worked their magic!!!  Gone are the days.......
My most favorite Stella Blue It comes together on this one and the quality is superb!
Scrumptious The proof is in the pudding!
